{{Quote|I am a huge Star Wars fan, so the chance to work with the original characters was too good to pass up, plus being part of the re-launch of the comics at Marvel is great to be a part of.|Terry Dodson|<ref name="Marvel.com" />}}
'''Terry Dodson''' is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] artist who penciled the [[Dark Force Rising (comics)|''Dark Force Rising'']] comic series in [[1997]]. He has also provided art for [[Mark Waid]]'s [[Star Wars: Princess Leia|'' Princess Leia'']] limited series. Moreover, Dodson has drawn the [[Wikipedia:Books-A-Million|Books-A-Million]] variant cover to the [[Shattered Empire 1|first issue]] of the [[Star Wars: Shattered Empire|''Shattered Empire'']] miniseries, and the [[Wikipedia:Comic Book Legal Defense Fund|CBLDF]] variant to [[Vader Down 1|''Vader Down'' 1]].

He recalled that as a child after seeing [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], he would buy anything related to the film, including the original [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel series]], which led to him buying comics. He even recalled his first drawings being that of [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]] and [[TIE/LN starfighter|TIE fighters]], so for him ''[[Star Wars]]'' and comic books are "intrinsically tied together."<ref name="Marvel.com">{{Marvel|url=news/comics/22973/sdcc_2014_princess_leia|text=SDCC 2014: Princess Leia}}</ref>

Dodson frequently collaborates with inker [[Rachel Dodson]], his wife. They are popular for regularly contributing covers for female superhero comics. Dodson's interior work includes [[Wikipedia:Warren Ellis|Warren Ellis's]] [[W:c:marvel:Storm Vol 1|''Storm'']] and [[W:c:marvel:Pryde and Wisdom Vol 1|''Pryde and Wisdom'']] limited series, [[W:c:dc:Harley Quinn Vol 1|''Harley Quinn'']], [[W:c:dc:Wonder Woman Vol 3|''Wonder Woman'']], [[W:c:marvel:Marvel Knights: Spider-Man Vol 1|''Marvel Knights: Spider-Man'']], [[W:c:marvel:Defenders Vol 4|''Defenders'']], and [[W:c:marvel:Avenging Spider-Man Vol 1|''Avenging Spider-Man'']] (penciling the story that reintroduced [[W:c:marvel:Carol Danvers (Earth-616)|Carol Danvers]] as Captain Marvel).

